         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>l.4. No definite solution has been found. Oliverio proposed <foreign xml:lang="la">e(x) h(onesta) m(issione)</foreign>. 
               Prof. E. Birley has suggested a cutter's error for <foreign xml:lang="la">Hem(esenorum)</foreign> or for 
                    <foreign xml:lang="la">e(quitatae) h(oc) m(onumentum) h(eredem) n(on) s(equetur)</foreign> but the latter seems much too sophisticated for this monument and is otherwise unattested in the province.
                    We suggest, very tentatively, <foreign xml:lang="la">e(quitum) H(e)m(esenorum)</foreign>.</p>
         </div>
         
